## Remarks  
 <span data-ttu-id="94989-102">Use um <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.PauseStoryboard> com um <xref:System.Windows.EventTrigger> ou <xref:System.Windows.Trigger> para pausar um Storyboard.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="94989-102">Use a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.PauseStoryboard> with an <xref:System.Windows.EventTrigger> or a <xref:System.Windows.Trigger> to pause a Storyboard.</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="94989-103"><xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.PauseStoryboard> afeta somente uma <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> quando ele estiver ativo (depois que o <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> é iniciado).</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="94989-103"><xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.PauseStoryboard> only affects a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> when it is active (after the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard> starts).</span></span>  
  
 <span data-ttu-id="94989-104">Para controlar um <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>, o <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.PauseStoryboard> deve fazer referência a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard.Name%2A> do <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard> que controla que <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="94989-104">To control a <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>, the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.PauseStoryboard> must reference the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard.Name%2A> of the <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.BeginStoryboard> that controls that <xref:System.Windows.Media.Animation.Storyboard>.</span></span> <span data-ttu-id="94989-105">Consulte [como: usar gatilhos de eventos para controlar um Storyboard após iniciar](~/docs/framework/wpf/graphics-multimedia/how-to-use-event-triggers-to-control-a-storyboard-after-it-starts.md) para obter um exemplo.</span><span class="sxs-lookup"><span data-stu-id="94989-105">See [How to: Use Event Triggers to Control a Storyboard After It Starts](~/docs/framework/wpf/graphics-multimedia/how-to-use-event-triggers-to-control-a-storyboard-after-it-starts.md) for an example.</span></span>  
  
